WorkItem.Description:
It would be extremely helpful to be able to unregister message recipients of a given type for scenarios in which a reference to the object(s) is not held. For example:

Messenger.Default.Unregister<TRecipient>();
Messenger.Default.Unregister<TRecipient,TMessage>();
... and other overloads

Another way to solve the problem is to expose a collection of registered recipients, so I can obtain a reference and then unregister using the existing Unregister methods.

Could you implement any of this?
